 <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0GNW0A6>	   <http://www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/dot_clear.gif>	Essay  Exclusive <http://www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/exclusive_sm.gif>
"It's All About the Madeleines," by Anne Ursu <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0GNW0A6>
"My novel, Spilling Clarence, is about memory -- or rather it's about remembering, which, I've come to believe, is a different kettle of fish," writes Anne Ursu in our exclusive essay. A selection of the 2002 Barnes & Noble Discover Great New Writers program, Spilling Clarence asks probing questions about the nature of memory -- and why we choose to forget. Read on to find out more about the origins of this very original debut, in "It's All About the Madeleines <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0GNW0A6>."	 
