Neate Wins Whitbread, Library of Congress Preserves Its Pages, Rowling Says <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap>	   <http://www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/dot_clear.gif>	Inside the Book Business
Neate Wins Whitbread, Library of Congress Preserves Its Pages, Rowling Says "I Do," and Melvillians "Call Me Ishmael"  <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap>
Patrick Neate takes the 2001 Whitbread Award, the Library of Congress takes steps to preserve its collection, J. K. Rowling gets married in Scotland, and Melvillians celebrate Moby-Dick in a 25-hour marathon reading. All this -- plus a look at the shortlist for the 2001 Barnes & Noble Discover Great New Writers Award -- in another look inside the book business <http://email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap>.	 
